body:
Alright, decided to look for a minimal reproduction case after all. This is what I came up with:
```java
package com.example

import static org.mockito.ArgumentMatchers.eq;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.spy;
import static org.mockito.Mockito.verify;

import org.testng.annotations.Test;

public final class MockitoIssue1254Test {
    @Test
    public void test() {
        Dummy d = spy(new Dummy());
        d.foo();
        verify(d).bar(eq("baz"));
    }

    static class Dummy {
        public void foo() {
            bar("baz");
        }

        // Also fails if public.
        void bar(String s) {}
    }
}
```

Causes:
```
Wanted but not invoked:
dummy.bar("baz");
-> at com.example.MockitoIssue1254Test$Dummy.bar(MockitoIssue1254Test.java:23)

However, there was exactly 1 interaction with this mock:
dummy.foo();
-> at com.example.MockitoIssue1254Test.test(MockitoIssue1254Test.java:13)
```

This test does pass with Mockito 2.11.0. It also passes with Mockito 2.12.0, provided `mockito-inline` is disabled.
